main event: An unidentified oval-shaped, white object was observed on radar equipment in Rogersville, Tennessee in June 1954.
interesting points: The object remained visible on the radar screen for 1-2 minutes before disappearing.
The report concludes the sighting was 'Reliable' and either a 'Balloon', 'Aircraft', or 'Unknown'.
The document appears to be a Project 10073 Record Card, which was part of the US Air Force's Project Blue Book investigation of UFO sightings.
The report does not contain any photographs, only textual details of the radar observation.
The radar contact occurred in the local time zone, but the specific time is not provided.
